ronko>{{cite book |last=Pronko|first=Leonard Cabell|title=The World of Jean Anouilh|year=1961|publisher=University of California Press|location=Los Angeles|pages=xix\u2013xxii}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Pucciani>{{cite book |last=Pucciani|first=Orestes|title=The French Theatre Since 1930|year=1954|publisher=Ginn|location=Boston|page=146}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Rocchi>{{cite book |last=Rocchi|first=Michel|title=''\"Jean Marie Lucien Pierre Anouilh\" in'' Twentieth-Century French Dramatists|year=2006|editor=Mary Anne O'Neil|publisher=Gale Biography in Context|location=Detroit}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Smith>{{cite book |last=Smith|first=Christopher Norman|title=Jean Anouilh, Life, Work, and Criticism|year=1985|publisher=York Press|location=London|isbn=0-919966-42-X}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Smith2426>{{cite book |last=Smith|title=Life, Work, and Criticism|pages=24\u201326}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Wiles>{{cite book |last=Wiles|first=David|title=''\"Politics.\" in'' Greek Theatre Performance: An Introduction|year=2000|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=0521648572|pages=63}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Jean Anouilh}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{IMDb name|0030478|name=Jean Anouilh}}\n{{Jean Anouilh}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anouilh, Jean}}\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:1987 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century French male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century French dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Modernist theatre]]\n[[Category:People from Bordeaux]]\n[[Category:Prix mondial Cino Del Duca winners]]\n[[Category:Laureates of the prix du Brigadier]]\n[[Category:French people of Basque descent]]\n", "name_user": "Clamias", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOriginal theatre productions: Paris", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Anouilh"}
{"title_page": "Penilee", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK place\n |country = Scotland\n |official_name= Penilee\n |gaelic_name= \n |scots_name= \n |population= \n |os_grid_reference= \n |coordinates = {{coord|55|51|08|N|4|22|12|W|display=inline,title}}\n |unitary_scotland = [[Politics of Glasgow|Glasgow City Council]]\n |lieutenancy_scotland = Glasgow\n |constituency_westminster= [[Glasgow South West (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South West]]\n |constituency_scottish_parliament= [[Glasgow Pollok (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Pollok]]\n |post_town= GLASGOW\n |postcode_district = G52 4\n |postcode_area= G\n |dial_code= 0141\n |static_image_name = Linburn Road (geograph 2089898).jpg \n |static_image_caption = Linburn Road\n}}\n'''Penilee''' is a small housing scheme and suburb on the southwestern edge of [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]].  The area is bounded to its east by the Glasgow suburbs of [[Cardonald]] and [[Hillington, Scotland|Hillington]], and to the west by the [[Renfrewshire]] border and the farms of North and South Arkleston.  The district's southern boundary forms Glasgow's border with the Renfrewshire settlement of [[Ralston, Renfrewshire|Ralston]]. The area is currently undergoing considerable residential redevelopment. One of Penilee\u2019s most notorious residents Reece Campbell, Rules the whole scheme with iron fist and takes out any nonces or grasses.\n\n==Initial development==\nPenilee was brought into the city of Glasgow with the boundary extension of 1938, and work began on a planned community to house workers at the nearby [[Hillington, Scotland|Hillington]] Industrial Estate. Some evidence of modernist architecture can be seen in the houses illustrated here, such as the flat roofs, horizontal windows and ship-deck balcony rails.\n\nAlthough most council house building was suspended for the duration of the [[Second World War]], an exception was made in the case of Penilee because of the demand for homes for workers at the numerous armaments factories at Hillington. Shortage of traditional materials meant that many of the wartime flats at Penilee were built of prefabricated materials such as foamslag.<ref>[https://www.theglasgowstory.com/image/?inum=TGSA05287&t=2 Penilee in Wartime (Glasgow City Archives, Department of Architectural and Civic Design, 1942)], The Glasgow Story</ref><ref>[https://www.theglasgowstory.com/image/?inum=TGSA05271&t=2 Maukinfauld Road (Glasgow City Archives, Department of Architectural and Civic Design, 1947)], The Glasgow Story</ref>\n\n[[File:Craigmuir Place (geograph 3434610).jpg|thumb|left|New housing at Craigmuir Place]]\nThe war also caused the cancellation of the 1941 census, but it is likely that wartime saw Glasgow's population reach its highest level as workers flooded in to take jobs in the city's numerous essential industries.\n\nThe area is served by [[Hillington West railway station]], the lines for which form the northern boundary of the neighbourhood.\n\n==Notable residents==\nScottish professional footballer [[Alan Hutton]] was born in Penilee.\n\nThree members of the music outfit [[The Orchids]] grew up and started the band in 1986 in Penilee. The guitarist Zal Cleminson of The Sensational Alex Harvey Band (SAHB) was also born in Penilee.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commonscat-inline}}\n\n{{Areas of Glasgow}}\n\n[[Category:Housing estates in Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Areas of Glasgow]]\n{{Glasgow-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox UK place\n |country = Scotland\n |official_name= Penilee\n |gaelic_name= \n |scots_name= \n |population= \n |os_grid_reference= \n |coordinates = {{coord|55|51|08|N|4|22|12|W|display=inline,title}}\n |unitary_scotland = [[Politics of Glasgow|Glasgow City Council]]\n |lieutenancy_scotland = Glasgow\n |constituency_westminster= [[Glasgow South West (UK Parliament constituency)|Glasgow South West]]\n |constituency_scottish_parliament= [[Glasgow Pollok (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Pollok]]\n |post_town= GLASGOW\n |postcode_district = G52 4\n |postcode_area= G\n |dial_code= 0141\n |static_image_name = Linburn Road (geograph 2089898).jpg \n |static_image_caption = Linburn Road\n}}\n'''Penilee''' is a small housing scheme and suburb on the southwestern edge of [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]].  The area is bounded to its east by the Glasgow suburbs of [[Cardonald]] and [[Hillington, Scotland|Hillington]], and to the west by the [[Renfrewshire]] border and the farms of North and South Arkleston.  The district's southern boundary forms Glasgow's border with the Renfrewshire settlement of [[Ralston, Renfrewshire|Ralston]]. The area is currently undergoing considerable residential redevelopment.\n\n==Initial development==\nPenilee was brought into the city of Glasgow with the boundary extension of 1938, and work began on a planned community to house workers at the nearby [[Hillington, Scotland|Hillington]] Industrial Estate. Some evidence of modernist architecture can be seen in the houses illustrated here, such as the flat roofs, horizontal windows and ship-deck balcony rails.\n\nAlthough most council house building was suspended for the duration of the [[Second World War]], an exception was made in the case of Penilee because of the demand for homes for workers at the numerous armaments factories at Hillington. Shortage of traditional materials meant that many of the wartime flats at Penilee were built of prefabricated materials such as foamslag.<ref>[https://www.theglasgowstory.com/image/?inum=TGSA05287&t=2 Penilee in Wartime (Glasgow City Archives, Department of Architectural and Civic Design, 1942)], The Glasgow Story</ref><ref>[https://www.theglasgowstory.com/image/?inum=TGSA05271&t=2 Maukinfauld Road (Glasgow City Archives, Department of Architectural and Civic Design, 1947)], The Glasgow Story</ref>\n\n[[File:Craigmuir Place (geograph 3434610).jpg|thumb|left|New housing at Craigmuir Place]]\nThe war also caused the cancellation of the 1941 census, but it is likely that wartime saw Glasgow's population reach its highest level as workers flooded in to take jobs in the city's numerous essential industries.\n\nThe area is served by [[Hillington West railway station]], the lines for which form the northern boundary of the neighbourhood.\n\n==Notable residents==\nScottish professional footballer [[Alan Hutton]] was born in Penilee.\n\nThree members of the music outfit [[The Orchids]] grew up and started the band in 1986 in Penilee. The guitarist Zal Cleminson of The Sensational Alex Harvey Band (SAHB) was also born in Penilee.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commonscat-inline}}\n\n{{Areas of Glasgow}}\n\n[[Category:Housing estates in Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Areas of Glasgow]]\n{{Glasgow-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:b0db:1500:64d8:5bf:3ac1:b2a6", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Added a resident)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penilee"}
{"title_page": "Love You More at Christmas Time", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 song by Kelly Rowland}}\n{{Infobox song \n| name       = Love You More at Christmas Time\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Kelly Rowland \u2013 Love You More at Christmas Time.jpg\n| alt        = \n| border     = yes\n| artist     = [[Kelly Rowland]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2019|11|22|mf=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Christmas music|Christmas]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=25}}\n| label      = [[KTR Records|KTR]]\n| writer     =\n* Kelly Rowland\n* [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]]\n* Angela Beyince\n* [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]]\n| producer   = Nash Overstreet\n| prev_title = [[Get It (Busta Rhymes song)|Get It]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Coffee (Kelly Rowland song)|Coffee]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = \n}}\n\"'''Love You More at Christmas Time'''\" is a [[Christmas music|Christmas song]] by American singer [[Kelly Rowland]]. It was released on November 22, 2019 as a single to promote ''Merry Liddle Christmas'', a holiday film in which Rowland stars in. The song was written by Rowland, [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]], Angela Beyince and [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]], while it was produced by Overstreet.\n\n==Release and composition==\nRowland first announced the song on [[Twitter]], posting on November 15 that the song was available for [[pre-order]] and also shared a teaser via [[Instagram]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=KELLYROWLAND|title=Christmas is coming early! Pre-save original music from my new holiday movie #MerryLiddleChristmas: https://equitydistro.ffm.to/2yndlgg|number=1195442122712735745|date=November 15, 2019|accessdate=December 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://foxy99.com/2019/11/22/kelly-rowland-releases-new-song-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland Releases New Song 'Love You More At Christmas Time'|last=Morgan|first=Glennisha|date=November 22, 2019|website=foxy99.com}}</ref> \"Love You More at Christmas Time\" was then released the next week and became available on all platforms on November 22, 2019.<ref name=AllPlatforms>{{cite tweet|user=KELLYROWLAND|title=Spreading love and happiness with new music from my movie #MerryLiddleChristmas! \u201cLove You More At Christmas Time\u201d is available now on all digital platforms! -xo https://equitydistro.ffm.to/2yndlgg \ud83c\udf81|number=1197744212243955712|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> It is the first original content and her third musical effort under the Christmas music genre overall as a soloist after her \"[[Do You Hear What I Hear?]]\" solo from the [[Destiny's Child]] album ''[[8 Days of Christmas]]'' (in 2001) and her cover of \"[[Wonderful Christmastime]]\" for the soundtrack to ''[[A Madea Christmas (film)|A Madea Christmas]]'' (in 2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/78230/destinys-child-celebrate-8-days-of-christmas|title=Destiny's Child Celebrate '8 Days Of Christmas'|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 2, 2001|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> Rowland co-wrote \"Love You More at Christmas Time\" with [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]], Angela Beyince and [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]].<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/122657329/credits|title=Kelly Rowland / Love You More at Christmas Time / Credits|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|language=en|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"RSI\">{{cite web|url=https://hamadamania.com/2019/11/22/kelly-rowland-unleashes-new-single-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland unleashes new single \u201cLove You More At Christmas Time\u201d|work=Hamada Mania Music Blog|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Love You More at Christmas Time\" runs for 3 minutes and 25 seconds.<ref name=Amazon>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Love-You-More-Christmas-Time/dp/B081K6N83N|title=Love You More At Christmas Time by Kelly Rowland on Amazon Music|website=[[Amazon.com]]|date=November 22, 2019}}</ref> The song is a \"[[mid-tempo]]\" [[Christmas music|Christmas]] song featuring an upbeat [[acoustic guitar]], [[jingle bells]] and lyrics about all the things that make the holidays special, including mistletoe and quality time with loved ones.<ref name=\"RatedRnb\">{{cite news|url=https://ratedrnb.com/2019/12/kelly-rowland-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland Releases New Song \u2018Love You More At Christmas Time\u2019|publisher=Rated R&B|last=Brissett|first=Danielle|date=December 2, 2019|accessdate=December 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'s Mike Wass called it \"cute, festive and loveable\", and observed that \"the seasonal bop has very genuine and rhythmic elements\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7903387/kelly-rowland-drops-love-you-even-more-at-christmas-time|title=Kelly Rowland's 'Love You More At Christmas Time' Is A Cute Seasonal Bop|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref> Gil Kaufman from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' said that \"Rowland imbues her new Christmas single with the spirit of Destiny Child's classic 8 Days of Christmas, swooningly delivering lines like 'Baby I believe in dreams/ And the joy the season brings/ You and me.'\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/holiday/8544506/2019-holiday-music-little-mix-mabel-cam-kelly-rowland|title=Festive Friday: Little Mix, Mabel, Cam, Kelly Rowland and More Debut New Holiday Music|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 22, 2018|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nD-Money of ''[[Soul Bounce]]'' wrote: \"The track has everything you'd expect from a Christmas song. Sleigh bells ring, snow and hot cocoa are mentioned, as is mistletoe and sitting with your boo by the fireside. However traditional the lyrics are, Kelly makes sure to keep things modern thanks to the slick R&B production. Guitar leads the way on the song, with warm bass, handclaps and finger snaps ushering in the soul of the season. Meanwhile, Kelly keeps things cozy with a mostly subdued vocal as the lyrics paint a vivid picture of holiday love.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Kelly Rowland Gets In The Holiday Spirit With \u2018Love You More At Christmas Time\u2019 |url=http://www.soulbounce.com/2019/11/kelly-rowland-love-you-more-at-christmas-time-audio/ |website=[[SoulBounce]] |date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n* [[Kelly Rowland]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals, background vocals, songwriting\n* Angela Beyince&nbsp;\u2013 background vocals, songwriting\n* [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]]&nbsp;\u2013 production, songwriting, mixing\n* [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriting\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Region\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Format\n! scope=\"col\" | Label\n! scope=\"col\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Worldwide\n| November 22, 2019\n| {{Hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[KTR Records|KTR]]\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=AllPlatforms></ref><ref name=\"iTunes world\">International releases of ''Love You More at Christmas Time'':\n* In the UK: {{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/love-you-more-at-christmas-time-single/1488131352|title=Love You More at Christmas Time- Single by Kelly Rowland|work=[[iTunes Store]] (UK)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]}}\n* In Australia: {{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/love-you-more-at-christmas-time-single/1488131352|title=Love You More at Christmas Time- Single by Kelly Rowland|work=[[iTunes Store]] (Australia)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]}}\n* In Canada: {{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/love-you-more-at-christmas-time-single/1488131352|title=Love You More at Christmas Time- Single by Kelly Rowland|work=[[iTunes Store]] (Canada)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]}}\n* In Spain: {{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/es/album/love-you-more-at-christmas-time-single/1488131352|title=Love You More at Christmas Time- Single by Kelly Rowland|work=[[iTunes Store]] (Spain)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]}}\n* In Germany: {{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/de/album/love-you-more-at-christmas-time-single/1488131352|title=Love You More at Christmas Time- Single by Kelly Rowland|work=[[iTunes Store]] (Germany)|publisher=[[Apple Inc]]}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kelly Rowland}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:American Christmas songs]]\n[[Category:Kelly Rowland songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kelly Rowland]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Shane Stevens (songwriter)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 song by Kelly Rowland}}\n{{Infobox song \n| name       = Love You More at Christmas Time\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Kelly Rowland \u2013 Love You More at Christmas Time.jpg\n| alt        = \n| border     = yes\n| artist     = [[Kelly Rowland]]\n| album      =\n| released   = {{start date|2019|11|22|mf=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Christmas music|Christmas]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=25}}\n| label      = [[KTR Records|KTR]]\n| writer     =\n* Kelly Rowland\n* [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]]\n* Angela Beyince\n* [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]]\n| producer   = Nash Overstreet\n| prev_title = [[Get It (Busta Rhymes song)|Get It]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Coffee (Kelly Rowland song)|Coffee]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = \n}}\n\"'''Love You More at Christmas Time'''\" is a [[Christmas music|Christmas song]] by American singer [[Kelly Rowland]]. It was released on November 22, 2019 as a single to promote ''Merry Liddle Christmas'', a holiday film in which Rowland stars in. The song was written by Rowland, [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]], Angela Beyince and [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]], while it was produced by Overstreet.\n\n==Release and composition==\nRowland first announced the song on [[Twitter]], posting on November 15 that the song was available for [[pre-order]] and also shared a teaser via [[Instagram]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=KELLYROWLAND|title=Christmas is coming early! Pre-save original music from my new holiday movie #MerryLiddleChristmas: https://equitydistro.ffm.to/2yndlgg|number=1195442122712735745|date=November 15, 2019|accessdate=December 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://foxy99.com/2019/11/22/kelly-rowland-releases-new-song-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland Releases New Song 'Love You More At Christmas Time'|last=Morgan|first=Glennisha|date=November 22, 2019|website=foxy99.com}}</ref> \"Love You More at Christmas Time\" was then released the next week and became available on all platforms on November 22, 2019.<ref name=AllPlatforms>{{cite tweet|user=KELLYROWLAND|title=Spreading love and happiness with new music from my movie #MerryLiddleChristmas! \u201cLove You More At Christmas Time\u201d is available now on all digital platforms! -xo https://equitydistro.ffm.to/2yndlgg \ud83c\udf81|number=1197744212243955712|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref> It is the first original content and her third musical effort under the Christmas music genre overall as a soloist after her \"[[Do You Hear What I Hear?]]\" solo from the [[Destiny's Child]] album ''[[8 Days of Christmas]]'' (in 2001) and her cover of \"[[Wonderful Christmastime]]\" for the soundtrack to ''[[A Madea Christmas (film)|A Madea Christmas]]'' (in 2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/78230/destinys-child-celebrate-8-days-of-christmas|title=Destiny's Child Celebrate '8 Days Of Christmas'|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=October 2, 2001|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref> Rowland co-wrote \"Love You More at Christmas Time\" with [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]], Angela Beyince and [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]].<ref name=\"Tidal\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/122657329/credits|title=Kelly Rowland / Love You More at Christmas Time / Credits|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|language=en|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"RSI\">{{cite web|url=https://hamadamania.com/2019/11/22/kelly-rowland-unleashes-new-single-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland unleashes new single \u201cLove You More At Christmas Time\u201d|work=Hamada Mania Music Blog|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n\"Love You More at Christmas Time\" runs for 3 minutes and 25 seconds.<ref name=Amazon>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Love-You-More-Christmas-Time/dp/B081K6N83N|title=Love You More At Christmas Time by Kelly Rowland on Amazon Music|website=[[Amazon.com]]|date=November 22, 2019}}</ref> It is a \"mid-tempo\" Christmas song featuring an upbeat acoustic guitar, jingle bells and lyrics aboutall the things that make the holidays special, including mistletoe and quality time with loved ones.<ref name=\"RatedRnb\">{{cite news|url=https://ratedrnb.com/2019/12/kelly-rowland-love-you-more-at-christmas-time/|title=Kelly Rowland Releases New Song \u2018Love You More At Christmas Time\u2019|publisher=Rated R&B|last=Brissett|first=Danielle|date=December 2, 2019|accessdate=December 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'s Mike Wass called it \"cute, festive and loveable\", and observed that \"the seasonal bop has very genuine and rhythmic elements\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7903387/kelly-rowland-drops-love-you-even-more-at-christmas-time|title=Kelly Rowland's 'Love You More At Christmas Time' Is A Cute Seasonal Bop|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=November 22, 2019|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref> Gil Kaufman from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' said that \"Rowland imbues her new Christmas single with the spirit of Destiny Child's classic 8 Days of Christmas, swooningly delivering lines like 'Baby I believe in dreams/ And the joy the season brings/ You and me.'\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/holiday/8544506/2019-holiday-music-little-mix-mabel-cam-kelly-rowland|title=Festive Friday: Little Mix, Mabel, Cam, Kelly Rowland and More Debut New Holiday Music|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 22, 2018|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nD-Money of ''[[Soul Bounce]]'' wrote: \"The track has everything you'd expect from a Christmas song. Sleigh bells ring, snow and hot cocoa are mentioned, as is mistletoe and sitting with your boo by the fireside. However traditional the lyrics are, Kelly makes sure to keep things modern thanks to the slick R&B production. Guitar leads the way on the song, with warm bass, handclaps and finger snaps ushering in the soul of the season. Meanwhile, Kelly keeps things cozy with a mostly subdued vocal as the lyrics paint a vivid picture of holiday love.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Kelly Rowland Gets In The Holiday Spirit With \u2018Love You More At Christmas Time\u2019 |url=http://www.soulbounce.com/2019/11/kelly-rowland-love-you-more-at-christmas-time-audio/ |website=[[SoulBounce]] |date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"Tidal\"/>\n\n* [[Kelly Rowland]]&nbsp;\u2013 lead vocals, background vocals, songwriting\n* Angela Beyince&nbsp;\u2013 background vocals, songwriting\n* [[Hot Chelle Rae|Nash Overstreet]]&nbsp;\u2013 production, songwriting, mixing\n* [[Shane Stevens (songwriter)|Shane Stevens]]&nbsp;\u2013 songwriting\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Region\