{"title_page": "Elk Rapids Public Schools", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox school\n | name                    = Elk Rapids Public Schools\n | logo                    = \n | motto                   = Where Excellence is a Tradition!\n | address                 = 707 E. Third Street\n | city                    = [[Elk Rapids, Michigan|Elk Rapids]]\n | state                   = [[Michigan]]\n | country                 = [[United States|U.S.]]\n | schooltype              = [[School District]]\n | fundingtype             = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n | school_board            = Holly Spencer, ''President''<br/>Jennifer Brown, ''Vice-President''<br/>Sherry Steffen-Detwiler, ''Secretary''<br/>Darryl Antcliff, ''Treasurer''<br/>Martha McGuire, ''Trustee''<br/>Carol Pressman, ''Trustee''<br/>Derek Morton, ''Trustee''\n | superintendent          = Tom Enslen\n | grades                  = PK-12\n | area                    = 125 sq mi\n | website                 = {{url|www.erschools.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Elk Rapids Public Schools''' is a [[State school|public school district]] based in [[Elk Rapids, Michigan]], in the United States. The district serves parts of [[Antrim County, Michigan|Antrim]], [[Grand Traverse County|Grand Traverse]], and [[Kalkaska County|Kalkaska]] counties, and is part of the larger [[Traverse Bay Area Intermediate School District]].<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=438dc453faf749d786e0c6e8be731cfd |title = Michigan Schools and Districts Map |publisher = Michigan Department of Technology, Management, and Budget |accessdate = April 28, 2020 }}</ref>. The school district has two [[elementary schools]], one [[middle school]], one [[high school]], and one [[alternative school]].<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.erschools.com/schools/ |title = Elk Rapids Public Schools -  Schools |publisher = Elk Rapids Public Schools |accessdate = April 28, 2020 }}</ref> As of 2018-2019, the district served 1,264 students and employed 67 teachers and 95 other staff members.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/districtsearch/district_detail.asp?start=0&ID2=2613050 |title = Elk Rapids Public Schools |publisher = National Center for Education Statistics |accessdate = April 28, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Schools ==\n*Lakeland Elementary School\n*Mill Creek Elementary School\n*Cherryland Middle School\n*[[Elk Rapids High School]]\n*Sunrise Academy ([[alternative school]])\n\n== Additional facilities ==\nAs a member of [[Traverse Bay Area Intermediate School District]] (TBAISD), Elk Rapids students have access to TBAISD facilities. Some high school students attend the TBAISD Career-Tech Center, a career and technical education school that offers education in 23 different career fields.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.tbaisd.org/career-tech-center/ |title = TBAISD CTC Information |publisher = TBAISD |accessdate = April 28, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:School districts in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Education in Antrim County, Michigan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n | name                    = Elk Rapids Public Schools\n | logo                    = \n | motto                   = Where Excellence is a Tradition!\n | address                 = 707 E. Third Street\n | city                    = [[Elk Rapids, Michigan|Elk Rapids]]\n | state                   = [[Michigan]]\n | country                 = [[United States|U.S.]]\n | schooltype              = [[School District]]\n | fundingtype             = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n | school_board            = Holly Spencer, ''President''<br/>Jennifer Brown, ''Vice-President''<br/>Sherry Steffen-Detwiler, ''Secretary''<br/>Darryl Antcliff, ''Treasurer''<br/>Martha McGuire, ''Trustee''<br/>Carol Pressman, '